    "what_description": "Euploca brachygyne is a species of flowering plant that belongs to the family Boraginaceae. It is an annual herb with erect or ascending stems, typically 15-40 cm long, and leaves that are oppositely arranged, simple, entire, and ovate or elliptic in shape, measuring 1-4 cm long and 0.5-2 cm wide. The flowers are small, blue-purple in color, and are arranged in axillary clusters; they have five petals, a calyx with five lobes, and a corolla tube that is 3-4 mm long. The plant produces four-angled, elongated fruits, approximately 10-15 mm long, containing four seeds each. Euploca brachygyne is native to Mexico and the southwestern United States.",
